{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-12",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_12_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 12 - Merry-Go-Round",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 4,
  "page_total": 5,
  "page_start_sec": 734.24,
  "page_end_sec": 975.36,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.759,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 734.24,
      "end": 735.81,
      "text": "\"'Didn't take her anywhere else first?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 736.7,
      "end": 736.7,
      "text": "No.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 737.64,
      "end": 738.34,
      "text": "It was like this."
    },
    {
      "start": 739.232,
      "end": 740.04,
      "text": "After we dropped you,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 740.24,
      "end": 741.48,
      "text": "I went on out Sacramento,"
    },
    {
      "start": 742.08,
      "end": 743.78,
      "text": "and when we got to Polk she rapped"
    },
    {
      "start": 743.78,
      "end": 745.42,
      "text": "on the glass and said she wanted to"
    },
    {
      "start": 745.42,
      "end": 745.94,
      "text": "get a newspaper,"
    },
    {
      "start": 746.24,
      "end": 749.16,
      "text": "so I stopped at the corner and whistled for a kid and"
    },
    {
      "start": 749.16,
      "end": 750.02,
      "text": "she got her paper."
    },
    {
      "start": 751.22,
      "end": 751.64,
      "text": "Which paper?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 752.4,
      "end": 752.9,
      "text": "The call.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 754.016,
      "end": 755.8,
      "text": "Then I went on out Sacramento,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 756.08,
      "end": 757.46,
      "text": "and just after we crossed"
    },
    {
      "start": 757.62,
      "end": 760.62,
      "text": "Van Ness she knocked on the glass again and said take her to the"
    },
    {
      "start": 760.68,
      "end": 761.14,
      "text": "Ferry Building."
    },
    {
      "start": 762.56,
      "end": 763.82,
      "text": "Was she excited or anything?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 764.96,
      "end": 765.86,
      "text": "Not so's I noticed.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 766.7,
      "end": 768.28,
      "text": "And when you got to the ferry building?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 769.14,
      "end": 769.84,
      "text": "She paid me off.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 769.98,
      "end": 770.6,
      "text": "That was all."
    },
    {
      "start": 772.096,
      "end": 773.5,
      "text": "Anybody waiting there for her?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 774.52,
      "end": 775.8,
      "text": "I didn't see them if they was.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 776.86,
      "end": 777.66,
      "text": "Which way did she go?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 778.52,
      "end": 779.06,
      "text": "At the ferry?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 779.66,
      "end": 780.16,
      "text": "I don't know."
    },
    {
      "start": 780.736,
      "end": 782.42,
      "text": "Maybe upstairs or toward the steps?"
    },
    {
      "start": 783.8,
      "end": 784.9,
      "text": "Take the newspaper with her?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 785.7,
      "end": 786.2,
      "text": "Yeah,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 786.4,
      "end": 788.66,
      "text": "she had it tucked under her arm when she paid me."
    },
    {
      "start": 789.92,
      "end": 792.24,
      "text": "With the pink sheet outside or one of the white?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 793.44,
      "end": 793.64,
      "text": "Hell,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 793.72,
      "end": 793.88,
      "text": "Cap,"
    },
    {
      "start": 794.14,
      "end": 795.02,
      "text": "I don't remember that."
    },
    {
      "start": 796.384,
      "end": 797.54,
      "text": "Spade thanked the chauffeur,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 797.62,
      "end": 797.8,
      "text": "said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 798.42,
      "end": 799.62,
      "text": "Get yourself a smoke,"
    },
    {
      "start": 799.8,
      "end": 801.32,
      "text": "and gave him a silver dollar."
    },
    {
      "start": 803.456,
      "end": 806.08,
      "text": "Spade bought a copy of the call and carried it into an",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 806.08,
      "end": 808.86,
      "text": "office-building vestibule to examine it out of the wind."
    },
    {
      "start": 809.56,
      "end": 812.22,
      "text": "His eyes ran swiftly over the front-page headlines"
    },
    {
      "start": 812.32,
      "end": 814.8,
      "text": "and over those on the second and third pages,"
    },
    {
      "start": 815.98,
      "end": 818.05,
      "text": "then paused for a moment under Suspect",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 818.58,
      "end": 820.84,
      "text": "Arrested as Counterfeiter on the fourth page,"
    },
    {
      "start": 821.66,
      "end": 823.32,
      "text": "and again on page 5 under",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 823.58,
      "end": 825.94,
      "text": "Bay Youth Seeks Death With Bullets."
    },
    {
      "start": 827.328,
      "end": 829.56,
      "text": "Pages 6 and 7 held nothing to interest him.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 830.82,
      "end": 831.22,
      "text": "On 8,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 831.4,
      "end": 834.0,
      "text": "three boys arrested as S.F."
    },
    {
      "start": 834.02,
      "end": 835.14,
      "text": "burglars after shooting"
    },
    {
      "start": 835.7,
      "end": 837.18,
      "text": "held his attention for a moment,"
    },
    {
      "start": 837.82,
      "end": 840.64,
      "text": "and after that nothing until he reached the 35th page,"
    },
    {
      "start": 841.32,
      "end": 842.5,
      "text": "which held news of the weather,"
    },
    {
      "start": 842.64,
      "end": 843.04,
      "text": "shipping,"
    },
    {
      "start": 843.28,
      "end": 843.56,
      "text": "produce,"
    },
    {
      "start": 843.86,
      "end": 844.14,
      "text": "finance,"
    },
    {
      "start": 844.5,
      "end": 844.9,
      "text": "divorces,"
    },
    {
      "start": 845.06,
      "end": 845.5,
      "text": "births,"
    },
    {
      "start": 845.5,
      "end": 845.76,
      "text": "marriages,"
    },
    {
      "start": 845.9,
      "end": 846.3,
      "text": "and deaths."
    },
    {
      "start": 847.27,
      "end": 848.98,
      "text": "He read the list of dead,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 849.16,
      "end": 851.46,
      "text": "passed over pages 36 and 37,"
    },
    {
      "start": 851.84,
      "end": 852.7,
      "text": "Financial News,"
    },
    {
      "start": 853.1,
      "end": 856.3,
      "text": "found nothing to stop his eyes on the 38th and last page,"
    },
    {
      "start": 856.54,
      "end": 857.14,
      "text": "sighed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 857.52,
      "end": 858.26,
      "text": "folded the newspaper,"
    },
    {
      "start": 858.58,
      "end": 860.88,
      "text": "put it in his coat pocket and rolled his cigarette."
    },
    {
      "start": 861.87,
      "end": 865.29,
      "text": "For five minutes he stood there in the office building vestibule,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 865.64,
      "end": 867.9,
      "text": "smoking and staring sulkily at nothing."
    },
    {
      "start": 869.14,
      "end": 870.78,
      "text": "Then he walked up to Stockton Street,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 871.04,
      "end": 872.94,
      "text": "hailed a taxi-cab and had himself"
    },
    {
      "start": 873.02,
      "end": 874.06,
      "text": "driven to the Coronet."
    },
    {
      "start": 874.71,
      "end": 878.34,
      "text": "He led himself into the building and into Bridget O'Shaughnessy's"
    },
    {
      "start": 878.34,
      "end": 880.12,
      "text": "apartment with the key she had given him."
    },
    {
      "start": 881.18,
      "end": 884.28,
      "text": "The blue gown she had worn the previous night was hanging across the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 884.36,
      "end": 885.02,
      "text": "foot of her bed."
    },
    {
      "start": 885.5,
      "end": 888.5,
      "text": "Her blue stockings and slippers were on the bedroom floor."
    },
    {
      "start": 889.54,
      "end": 892.74,
      "text": "The polychrome box that had held jewelry and had been in the dressing",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 892.88,
      "end": 895.64,
      "text": "table drawer now stood empty on the dressing table's top."
    },
    {
      "start": 896.992,
      "end": 897.92,
      "text": "Spade frowned at it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 897.96,
      "end": 899.4,
      "text": "ran his tongue across his lips,"
    },
    {
      "start": 899.62,
      "end": 900.4,
      "text": "strolled through"
    },
    {
      "start": 900.4,
      "end": 902.74,
      "text": "the rooms looking around but not touching anything,"
    },
    {
      "start": 902.98,
      "end": 903.96,
      "text": "then left the"
    },
    {
      "start": 904.18,
      "end": 905.66,
      "text": "coronet and went downtown again."
    },
    {
      "start": 907.52,
      "end": 911.18,
      "text": "In the doorway of the building where Spade had his offices he came",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 911.3,
      "end": 913.82,
      "text": "face to face with the boy he had left at Gutman's."
    },
    {
      "start": 914.19,
      "end": 915.18,
      "text": "The boy put"
    },
    {
      "start": 915.3,
      "end": 916.5,
      "text": "himself in Spade's path,"
    },
    {
      "start": 916.72,
      "end": 917.58,
      "text": "blocking the entrance,"
    },
    {
      "start": 917.76,
      "end": 918.06,
      "text": "and said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 918.92,
      "end": 919.28,
      "text": "\"'Come on.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 919.4,
      "end": 920.64,
      "text": "He wants to see you.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 921.4,
      "end": 923.64,
      "text": "The boy's hands were in his overcoat pockets.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 924.7,
      "end": 925.74,
      "text": "His pockets bulged",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 925.86,
      "end": 928.1,
      "text": "more than his hands need have made them bulge."
    },
    {
      "start": 929.024,
      "end": 929.96,
      "text": "Spade grinned and",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 930.02,
      "end": 930.74,
      "text": "said mockingly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 932.02,
      "end": 934.02,
      "text": "I didn't expect you till 5.25.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 935.12,
      "end": 937.12,
      "text": "I hope I haven't kept you waiting long.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 937.68,
      "end": 940.84,
      "text": "The boy raised his eyes to Spade's mouth and spoke"
    },
    {
      "start": 940.84,
      "end": 943.3,
      "text": "in the strained voice of one in physical pain."
    },
    {
      "start": 944.52,
      "end": 945.18,
      "text": "You louse!",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 945.34,
      "end": 946.76,
      "text": "Keep on riding me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 946.92,
      "end": 949.2,
      "text": "and you're going to be picking iron out of your navel."
    },
    {
      "start": 950.4,
      "end": 951.12,
      "text": "Spade chuckled.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 951.84,
      "end": 952.8,
      "text": "The cheaper the crook,"
    },
    {
      "start": 952.86,
      "end": 954.08,
      "text": "the gaudier the patter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 954.76,
      "end": 955.5,
      "text": "he said cheerfully."
    },
    {
      "start": 956.1,
      "end": 956.28,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 956.46,
      "end": 957.06,
      "text": "let's go."
    },
    {
      "start": 958.34,
      "end": 960.26,
      "text": "They walked up Sutter Street side by side.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 960.88,
      "end": 963.22,
      "text": "The boy kept his hands in his overcoat pockets."
    },
    {
      "start": 964.26,
      "end": 966.42,
      "text": "They walked a little more than a block in silence.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 967.6,
      "end": 969.1,
      "text": "Then Spade asked pleasantly,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 969.75,
      "end": 971.98,
      "text": "How long have you been off the lay?"
    },
    {
      "start": 972.9,
      "end": 975.36,
      "text": "The boy did not show that he had heard the question.",
      "para_break": true
    }
  ]
}